description: Le processus de décentralisation est avancé en république du Congo, mais très faible au niveau des structures communales. L'objectif général du projet, dont ce marché fait partie, est d'améliorer les conditions de vie et l'attractivité des villes de Nkayi et Owando. L'assainissement a été choisi comme domaine d'application du renforcement de capacités des autorités locales.La convention de financement comporte trois objectifs spécifiques:— le 1er, objet du présent marché, est le renforcement des collectivités locales;— le 2nd relève des travaux d'assainissement. The project will promote Sustainable Energy in Tajikistan by supporting the institutional, legal and regulatory environment in the energy sector, improving the capacities and efficiency of the Ministry of Energy and Water Resources (MoEWR), Barqi Tajik operators (BT Generation, Transmission Operator and System Operators), as well as the Electricity Regulation Department of the Antimonopoly Service. This will make the electricity market fairer and more transparent, based on non-discriminatory and cost-reflective tariffs and thus attractive for the private sector, and able to cope with the requirements of an efficient regional power market. The project will enhance the interaction and coordination between energy and water sector stakeholders, and support activities that will reduce greenhouse gas emissions and improve climate change adaptation. 
     The Action is aligned with the 2030 Agenda as well as the EU’s new Global Gateway strategy and the European Green Deal.
title: Technical Assistance package for the Sustainable Energy Support Programme in Tajikistan

results.content: TA towards Developing a Strategy of Construction and Demolition Waste (C&DW) Management According to EU Circular Economy Package and Its Implementation (StraCDW)

description: The project aims to achieve circularity of C&DW management in Türkiye, Strategy of C&DW has the main objective to support Türkiye’s efforts towards zero waste management via developing a C&DW management strategy in line with EU circular economy policies. To accomplish this objective technical capacity on management of C&DW will be increased through current situation assessment of C&DW in Türkiye and preparation of Policy Recommendation Paper (PRP) and guidelines that provide a methodology for demolition or renovation of buildings and infrastructures, as well as, training and awareness raising activities in 7 different geographical regions of Türkiye. Last but not least, in 12 different areas, recommendations and methodologies defined in the PRP will be implemented on site.
title: TA towards Developing a Strategy of Construction and Demolition Waste (C&DW) Management According to EU Circular Economy Package and Its Implementation (StraCDW)

results.summary: Technical Assistance for Turkiye in Horizon Europe
results.content: Technical Assistance for Turkiye in Horizon Europe

description: Integration of Turkish Research Area (TARAL) into European Research Area (ERA) by increased participation in Framework Programmes is a critical pillar supporting innovation and technology development in Türkiye. Further to Türkiye’s previous participation in EU programmes, there is still need to increase awareness, explore funding mechanisms and increase project applications in EU programmes among potential beneficiaries. Within the scope of the project, Türkiye’s performance in H2020 will be analysed through current situation assessment and roadmaps will be developed to increase participation in Horizon Europe.  According to results of assessment and roadmaps, capacity development trainings will be provided for the target groups, which will play an active role for the improvement of the R&D sector and ecosystem in Türkiye. Also, several knowledge diffusion and networking activities will be organized to increase awareness on Horizon Europe.
title: Technical Assistance for Turkiye in Horizon Europe

description: Communication is key to support the achievement of EU objectives and the pursuit of EU values in India. As such, strategic communication activities on the Global Gateway priorities, while including a Team Europe approach with a Global Gateway branding will a) provide a link between policies and development, in a tangible and relatable manner on key Global Gateway priority areas and b) will make a wider audience understand why the EU’s partnership with India is positive and of relevance. The overall objective of the contract is to increase the awareness and perception of the EU, with  a ‘whole of the EU approach’. The communication activities will be geared to ensure a greater EU-brand recognition (‘Team Europe/Global Gateway’)  among the general public as a key contributor to India’s national development and its international/regional ambitions, and as a key ally for India on the international stage to tackle global problems that fall with the realm of the 7 identified priority areas.
title: EU-India Strategic Communication in Support of Global Gateway

results.content: Eastern Partnership Civil Society Facility Regional Technical Assistance to Build Civil Society Capacities

description: This Regional Technical Assistance project will contribute to strengthening and promoting the role of civil society in reforms and democratic changes in the Eastern Partnership countries, creating synergies between various EU-funded bilateral and regional initiatives for civil society organisations. It will implement and support the following type of activities:• regional civil society capacity building activities, including Civil Society Fellowships, e-Learning and training activities, etc.;• civic tech activities across the region including hackathons, e-Participation initiatives, etc.;• communication activities in order to increase the public awareness of CSOs, improve their public image and promote EU support to civil society in a more consistent and coherent manner;• conduct studies, mappings and research on civil society issues across the region.
title: Eastern Partnership Civil Society Facility Regional Technical Assistance to Build Civil Society Capacities

results.summary: Latin America Investment Facility (LAIF) and Caribbean Investment Facility (CIF) - Joint Technical Assistance
results.content: Latin America Investment Facility (LAIF) and Caribbean Investment Facility (CIF) - Joint Technical Assistance

description: Blending is defined as the strategic use of a limited amount of grants to mobilize non-grant resources from partner Financial Institutions and the private and/or public sector, for enhanced development impact of investment projects. The EU has two blending facilities for the Latin American and Caribbean region, LAIF and CIF. While the two Facilities are managed independently, have independent pipelines and some variety in sectors of concentration, both are managed by the same team in INTPA B1, share their main objectives and could benefit from a shared presence in social media and at regional events and a common monitoring system. In order to maximise strategic alignment and synergies between the two facilities, and to share knowledge and tools, it has been decided to contract a common Technical Assistance.
title: Latin America Investment Facility (LAIF) and Caribbean Investment Facility (CIF) - Joint Technical Assistance
